cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.AI 

This paper deals with learning patient representations from clinical notes using deep learning techniques, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of stacked denoising autoencoder and paragraph vector model, which are deep learning models, and their comparison with sparse representations obtained from a bag-of-words model, indicating the relevance of cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also proposes novel techniques for model interpretability, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the model in predicting patient mortality, primary diagnostic and procedural category, and gender, which can be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
